  "prompt": "What is the best clinic for systemic Lupus in United States?",
  "response": "Identifying the \"best\" clinic for systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) in the United States can depend on various factors, including the specific needs of the patient, location, and the expertise of healthcare providers. However, several renowned clinics and institutions are recognized for their expertise in lupus and autoimmune diseases:\n\n1. **Johns Hopkins Lupus Center** (Baltimore, MD) - Known for its comprehensive research, education programs, and specialized care in lupus.\n\n2. **Lupus Center at NYU Langone Health** (New York, NY) - Offers advanced treatment options and has a dedicated team focusing on lupus.\n\n3. **Cleveland Clinic** (Cleveland, OH) - Recognized for its rheumatology department and research in autoimmune diseases, including lupus.\n\n4. **Mayo Clinic** (Rochester, MN) - Known for its patient-centered approach and expertise in a wide range of medical conditions, including lupus.\n\n5. **Duke University Hospital** (Durham, NC) - Offers specialized care in rheumatology and has a dedicated lupus program.\n\nWhen seeking care for systemic lupus, it\u2019s crucial to consider factors such as the clinic's access to specialists, ongoing clinical trials, patient reviews, and whether they are affiliated with academic research institutions. It may also be beneficial to consult with local rheumatologists for recommendations based on individual circumstances.",
